UID:90222-1781434800-1781440200@bangaloreinternationalcentre.org
SUMMARY:Stamp Stories
DESCRIPTION:A stamp\, some ink\, and a blank postcard. \nIn this hands-on workshop\, children carve their own stamps\, press them into paper\, and walk away with handmade postcards ready to be sent to someone they love. \nBring your curiosity\, and a willingness to make a mess. Limited to fifteen spots. \n\nAround the World in 50 Sundays is a journey that begins\, not with a ticket\, but with opening a book. In a city like Bangalore where families are always in motion\, the BIC Library hopes to offer stillness and a quiet\, welcoming space for both parents and children where reading becomes a shared experience. \nEvery Sunday\, we open our doors to invite you into a library that listens; building a rhythm of return\, a habit of joy and a new community bound not just by books\, but by the weekly ritual of reading together. \nWe welcome your ideas and input. If you have suggestions for children’s events or activities that align with this vision\, we’d love to hear from you. Please reach out to us at library@bangaloreinternationalcentre.org \n\n\nSupported by:\n\n
URL:https://bangaloreinternationalcentre.org/event/stamp-stories/
LOCATION:Bangalore International Centre\, 7\, 4th Main Road\, Domlur II Stage\, Bangalore\, Karnataka\, 560071\, India
CATEGORIES:Around the World in 50 Sundays,Design,Visual Arts,Workshops
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://bangaloreinternationalcentre.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/Thumbnail_SS.jpg
END:VEVENT
