UID:90553-1781460000-1781465400@bangaloreinternationalcentre.org
SUMMARY:To the Moon and Beyond
DESCRIPTION:The new space race is underway. \nNASA’s Artemis II swung four astronauts around the Moon this April. India’s Chandrayaan-3 landed near the lunar south pole a few years ago. And China has been quietly building the most ambitious lunar programme of any nation thus far. The moon has turned from symbol to destination through missions\, timelines\, and competing national interests. \nIn this conversation\, Srinivasan Chandrasekhar\, Jatan Mehta\, and Jahnavi Phalkey examine what this moment means: the technological achievement\, the geopolitical contest\, and the question of who sets the rules when the moon’s resources are finally within reach. \nThe session will conclude with an audience Q&A. \n
URL:https://bangaloreinternationalcentre.org/event/to-the-moon-and-beyond/
LOCATION:Bangalore International Centre\, 7\, 4th Main Road\, Domlur II Stage\, Bangalore\, Karnataka\, 560071\, India
CATEGORIES:Science,Society,Technology
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://bangaloreinternationalcentre.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/thumbnail-moon.jpg
END:VEVENT
